<subSubSection id="DAAD6DC69476FFF2FF2DFB5D9109FE2B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="92083E4D9476FFF2FF2DFB5D9109FE2B" blockId="3.[192,802,1223,1890]" lastBlockId="3.[830,1440,199,469]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
DIAGNOSIS. Total length 
<quantity id="554F93A89476FFF2FE3BFB5D9605FB20" box="[470,589,1223,1246]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="65.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="40.0">40–90 mm</quantity>
(except 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FD42FB5D9511FB03" authority="Vachon, 1949" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1949" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villiersi">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FD42FB5D9769FB20" box="[687,801,1223,1246]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. villiersi</emphasis>
Vachon, 1949
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FE79FB7C96E7FB03" authority="Lourenco, 2001" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="2001" box="[404,687,1254,1277]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clevai">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FE79FB7C95BCFB03" box="[404,500,1254,1277]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. clevai</emphasis>
Lourenço, 2001
</taxonomicName>
); carapace trapezoidal, in lateral view preocular area not distinctly inclined towards anterior margin, level with or higher than postocular area; surface of carapace conspicuously granular, with only anterior median carinae developed, anterior part of carapace glossy; ventral aspect of cheliceral fixed finger with two denticles; tergites with three carinae of which lateral pair on I and II inconspicuous; pectines with fulcra, hirsute; hemispermatophore flagelliform, capsule with 4 lobes, lobes separated from flagellum, basal lobe small, knob-like; sternum subtriangular; metasomal segments I–III with 8–10 carinae; metasoma II as wide as other metasomal segments; metasoma V with enlarged &quot;lobate&quot; dentition on ventrolateral carinae; telson without subaculear tubercle, with long curved aculeus, longer than vesicle (except 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FEFAF94A962CF919" authority="Hendrixson, 2006" authorityName="Hendrixson" authorityYear="2006" box="[279,612,1744,1767]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buettikeri">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FEFAF94A95D4F919" box="[279,412,1744,1767]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. buettikeri</emphasis>
Hendrixson, 2006
</taxonomicName>
); all segments of metasoma hirsute, with long setae in both sexes, dentate margin of movable finger of pedipalp with 9–12 rows of granules, each row equipped with one internal accessory granule, and with (
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FE75F8D1967BF89C" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[408,563,1867,1890]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptochelys">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FE75F8D1967BF89C" box="[408,563,1867,1890]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. leptochelys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex) or without (
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FCAAFF5D9783FF20" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[839,971,199,222]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenicola">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FCAAFF5D9783FF20" box="[839,971,199,222]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. arenicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex) one external accessory granule, 4 terminal and one basal terminal granules present; trichobothrial pattern orthobothriotaxic 
<typeStatus id="4D0C80EF9476FFF2FB1FFE9E9168FEE5" box="[1266,1312,260,283]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
A; dorsal trichobothria of femur arranged in β- configuration; pedipalp patella with 7 external trichobothria; pedipalp femur with trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FB9CFEF89036FE87" box="[1137,1150,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">d</emphasis>
<subScript id="0E333C089476FFF2FB92FEF790C0FE82" attach="left" box="[1151,1160,365,380]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">2</subScript>
on dorsal surface; 
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FA85FEF8913DFE87" box="[1384,1397,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">d</emphasis>
<subScript id="0E333C089476FFF2FA98FEF79136FE82" attach="left" box="[1397,1406,365,380]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">2</subScript>
of pedipalp patella present; patella trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FAB2FE1B9124FE66" box="[1375,1388,385,408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">d</emphasis>
<subScript id="0E333C089476FFF2FA81FE11913DFE64" attach="left" box="[1388,1397,395,410]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">3</subScript>
internal to dorsomedian carina; tibial spurs present on legs III–IV but could be reduced or absent on leg III.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DAAD6DC69476FFF2FCD3FE669076FACE" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="92083E4D9476FFF2FCD3FE6690ABFD35" blockId="3.[830,1442,508,1328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
COMMENTS. Many of the diagnostic characters applied to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FC05FD809004FDCF" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[1000,1100,538,561]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FC05FD809004FDCF" box="[1000,1100,538,561]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other buthid genera seem to be plesiomorphic, so the genus is not strongly supported by derived characters. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FB20FDC29178FD91" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[1229,1328,600,623]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FB20FDC29178FD91" box="[1229,1328,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be a paraphyletic assemblage of taxa containing several distinct lineages. It is beyond the scope of this paper to completely revise and divide 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FB95FD2E9093FD35" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[1144,1243,692,715]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FB95FD2E9093FD35" box="[1144,1243,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92083E4D9476FFF2FC83FD48904EFC03" blockId="3.[830,1442,508,1328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FC83FD489169FD17" authority="Zambre et Lourenco, 2010" authorityName="Zambre et Lourenco" authorityYear="2010" box="[878,1313,722,745]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agarwali">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FC83FD4897B8FD17" box="[878,1008,722,745]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. agarwali</emphasis>
Zambre et Lourenço, 2010
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="EAA07EDD9476FFF2FA84FD4891E8FD17" box="[1385,1440,722,745]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">India</collectingCountry>
definitely does not belong in 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FB90FD6B9097FCF6" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[1149,1247,753,776]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FB90FD6B9097FCF6" box="[1149,1247,753,776]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it differs in the characters cited in the diagnosis above as well as in other aspects of its morphology, mainly in shape of the pedipalp segments. The taxonomic position of 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FA64FCD790D9FC7D" authority="Lourenco et Qi, 2007" authorityName="Lourenco et Qi" authorityYear="2007" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maliensis">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FA64FCD797EBFC7D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">B. maliensis</emphasis>
Lourenço et Qi, 2007
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="EAA07EDD9476FFF2FB38FCF6914FFC7D" box="[1237,1287,876,899]" name="Serbia" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mali</collectingCountry>
is also doubtful. It has a short aculeus, the anterior part of the carapace is probably not glossy, the movable finger of pedipalp has nearly linear rows of granules, and the total length is 29.8 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92083E4D9476FFF2FC83FB9F9076FACE" blockId="3.[830,1442,508,1328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
It appears that the most reliable diagnostic character for 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FC88FBBE9780FBC5" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[869,968,1060,1083]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FC88FBBE9780FBC5" box="[869,968,1060,1083]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the presence of 9–12 rows of granules on the movable finger. The only species for which this character is inapplicable is 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FB8BFBFB904AFB69" authority="Lourenco et Leguin, 2009" authorityName="Lourenco et Leguin" authorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FB8BFBFB917AFB86" box="[1126,1330,1121,1144]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus williamsi</emphasis>
Lourenço et Leguin, 2009
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry id="EAA07EDD9476FFF2FB79FB1A91D4FB69" box="[1172,1436,1152,1175]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
, described from three females that have 6 or 7 rows of granules on the movable finger. We are convinced, however, that this species does not belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FCD3FB6097E9FAEF" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1910" box="[830,929,1274,1297]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FCD3FB6097E9FAEF" box="[830,929,1274,1297]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but probably to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="55B745CE9476FFF2FB3EFB60907FFACE" authority="Levy, Amitai et Shulov, 1973" authorityName="Levy, Amitai et Shulov" authorityYear="1973" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Vachoniolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0C3E25F9476FFF2FB3EFB609110FAEF" box="[1235,1368,1274,1297]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Vachoniolus</emphasis>
Levy, Amitai et Shulov, 1973
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
